extends Enum<Country>
    Enumeration for all current ISO 3166-1 ALPHA2 country codes using 2 letters, with the exception of PS and TW which are overridden by GBIF. Older country codes will be supported soon, @see #isDeprecated(). All user assigned codes (e.g. XX and QS) are mapped to the single enum USER_DEFINED. The enumeration maps to ALPHA3 3-letter codes.
